==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Curves_Line.svg|24px]] '''Curves Line''' tool creates a parametric line between two vertices.

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Select two vertices in the [[3D_View|3D view]].
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Curves_Line.svg|16px]] [[Curves_Line|Parametric line]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Curves → [[Image:Curves_Line.svg|16px]] Parametric line}} option from the menu.
# A '''Line''' object is created.

==Properties== <!--T:9-->

See also: [[Property_editor|Property editor]].

A '''Line''' object is derived from an [[App_FeaturePython|App FeaturePython]] object and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:

===Data===

{{TitleProperty|Line}}

* {{PropertyData|Vertex1|LinkSub}}: The first referenced vertex.
* {{PropertyData|Vertex2|LinkSub}}: The second referenced vertex.

